data.enText: to move soldiers or weapons into a position where they are ready for military action

data.chText: 那个地区部署了2 000人的部队。
data.enText: 2 000 troops were deployed in the area.

data.chText: 沿边境至少部署了5 000枚导弹。
data.enText: At least 5 000 missiles were deployed along the border.

simple_means.memory_skill: de 使… + ploy 用 → 使用〔部队〕→ 调度；部署〔部队〕

ex.chText: 国防部决定部署新的导弹系统。
ex.enText: The defense department decided to deploy a new missile system.
The infantry was deployed at the foot of the mountain.

ex.chText: 他已经安排了周末和新客户们开会。
ex.enText: He has arranged a meeting with his new clients for the weekend.

ex.chText: 该部门会安排一辆出租车去机场接那三位外国专家。
ex.enText: The department will arrange a taxi to meet those three foreign experts at the airport.

ex.chText: 请将书架上的这些书整理好。
ex.enText: Please arrange these books on the shelf in order.

synonyms.bx: 指根据目的和计划调整事物的时间、空间或顺序。

ex.chText: 为了丰富我们的校园生活，学生会已经组织了一个戏剧俱乐部。
ex.enText: The students' union has organized a drama club in order to enrich our campus life.

ex.chText: 他们花了3个月的时间组织这次竞赛。
ex.enText: It took them 3 months to organize this competition.

synonyms.bx: 指按计划或需要把人或事物安排、组织成一个整体，既可指筹备具体活动，又可指使抽象事物更有条理。

tr: place troops or weapons in battle formation

example: The U.S. deploys its weapons in the Middle East

value.def: To deploy troops or military resources means to organize or position them so that they are ready to be used.

example.ex: The president said he had no intention of deploying ground troops.
example.tran: 总统称并不打算部署地面部队。

example.ex: ...the US-made Patriot anti-missile system which was deployed in the Gulf war.
example.tran: 在海湾战争中部署的美国制造的“爱国者”反导弹系统

value.tran: 部署，调集（部队或军事力量）

partsOfSpeech.dec: de 使… + ploy 用 → 使用〔部队〕→ 调度；部署〔部队〕
em 使… + ploy 用 → 使用 → 雇用
ex 出 + ploit 用 → 利用出来 → 开发利用
re 重新 + deploy 调度；部署（部队）→ 重新部署
